## 10. Direct `SPIEC-EASI` example

`SPIEC-EASI` is designed for sparse and compositionally robust inference of microbial ecological association networks. It combines compositional data transformations with sparse graphical model estimation.

```r
library(SpiecEasi)
library(phyloseq)
library(igraph)

# Example using a phyloseq object
se_fit <- spiec.easi(
  ps,
  method = "mb",
  lambda.min.ratio = 1e-2,
  nlambda = 20,
  pulsar.params = list(rep.num = 50)
)

# Extract adjacency matrix
adj <- getRefit(se_fit)

# Convert to igraph object
g <- adj2igraph(adj)

plot(g)
```

### Method options

```text
method = "mb"       Meinshausen-Bühlmann neighborhood selection
method = "glasso"   graphical lasso inverse covariance estimation
```

The selected method, lambda path, and stability-selection parameters should be reported.

