## 11. Extracting graph metrics with `igraph`

Once a network is represented as an `igraph` object, general graph metrics can be extracted.

```r
library(igraph)

node_metrics <- tibble(
  taxon = V(g)$name,
  degree = degree(g),
  betweenness = betweenness(g),
  closeness = closeness(g),
  eigenvector = eigen_centrality(g)$vector,
  component = components(g)$membership
)

head(node_metrics)
```

Global network metrics:

```r
network_metrics <- tibble(
  nodes = vcount(g),
  edges = ecount(g),
  density = edge_density(g),
  transitivity = transitivity(g, type = "global"),
  average_degree = mean(degree(g)),
  components = components(g)$no
)

network_metrics
```

