## 14. Positive and negative associations

Some methods return signed associations. Positive and negative edges should be interpreted carefully.

| Edge sign | Possible interpretation | Caution |
|---|---|---|
| Positive | Shared niche, co-occurrence, similar response to host/environment | May reflect confounding or compositional effects |
| Negative | Exclusion pattern, contrasting niche, inverse response | Does not prove competition |

Suggested wording:

```text
Positive and negative edges were interpreted as statistical association patterns. They were not interpreted as direct cooperation or competition without additional biological evidence.
```

